</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/thr/news/~4/f3a3-YZGIC0" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:33:"http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:18:"Hollywood Reporter";}s:32:"71d6056974f2d504e7fe5c181180ac06";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:81:"Tokyoflash Kisai Adjust watch tells time with triangles, in trippy colors (video)";s:4:"link";s:91:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/22/tokyoflash-kisai-adjust-watch-tells-time-with-triangles/";s:6:"author";s:10:"Jon Fingas";s:4:"date";i:1358838000;s:7:"content";s:1780:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/22/tokyoflash-kisai-adjust-watch-tells-time-with-triangles/"><img alt="Tokyoflash Kisai Adjust watch tells time with triangles, in trippy colors video" data-src-height="303" data-src-width="620" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/01/tokyoflash-kisai-adjust.jpg"></a></p><p> It almost goes without saying <a href="http://www.engadget.com/tag/Tokyoflash/">Tokyoflash</a> watches aren't always very <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/24/tokyoflash-kisai-seven-tells-time-with-tron-design-makes-fan-dr/">scrutable</a>. The company's newly launched Kisai Adjust, however, is thankfully one of the more legible examples -- as the name suggests, it even goes out of its way to accommodate the wearer. The fan-designed timepiece uses LED-lit triangles to offer the time and date in any one of six colors, including a slightly mesmerizing "candy," with the option to display digits horizontally in those moments it's not on a wrist. It's USB-rechargeable, too, for those averse to wall outlets; expect about a month of dazzling (or confusing) friends between battery top-ups. Tokyoflash is selling the Kisai Adjust today, although you'll want to buy the watch within the first 48 hours to pay $149 instead of the regular $179. Head past the break for a video that helps explain the Adjust's changeable ways.</p><br><div align="center"> </div><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/wearables/" rel="tag">Wearables</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/22/tokyoflash-kisai-adjust-watch-tells-time-with-triangles/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="http://www.tokyoflash.com/en/watches/kisai/adjust" target="_blank">Tokyoflash</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:8:"Engadget";}s:32:"f4f6c4c4a957ec6095f97c5e1f58edc3";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:37:"Charlie Victor Romeo: Sundance Review";s:4:"link";s:66:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/thr/news/~3/Cbi1AV8BJ1A/story01.htm";s:6:"author";s:11:"John DeFore";s:4:"date";i:1358837624;s:7:"content";s:2525:"<img src="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/sites/default/files/2013/01/CharlieVictorRomeo.jpg"><br>An acclaimed Off-Broadway play about aircraft emergencies makes an effective transition to the screen.<p><a href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/charlie-victor-romeo-sundance-film-414218" target="_blank">read more</a></p><img width="1" height="1" src="http://rss.feedsportal.com/c/34793/f/641578/s/27c3bb39/mf.gif" border="0"><div><table border="0"><tr><td valign="middle"><a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/viral/sendEmail.cfm?lang=en&amp;title=Charlie+Victor+Romeo%3A+Sundance+Review&amp;link=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hollywoodreporter.com%2Freview%2Fcharlie-victor-romeo-sundance-film-414218" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/images/emailthis2.gif" border="0"></a></td><td valign="middle"><a href="http://res.feedsportal.com/viral/bookmark.cfm?title=Charlie+Victor+Romeo%3A+Sundance+Review&amp;link=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hollywoodreporter.com%2Freview%2Fcharlie-victor-romeo-sundance-film-414218" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/images/bookmark.gif" border="0"></a></td></tr></table></div><div>
