</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/thr/news/~4/EoczTlz36mo" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:33:"http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:18:"Hollywood Reporter";}s:32:"683eca336a8560106a7a14cfa7cc1189";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:76:"White Samsung ATIV Smart PC launches in South Korea, remains the same inside";s:4:"link";s:75:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/white-samsung-ativ-smart-pc-south-korea/";s:6:"author";s:13:"Edgar Alvarez";s:4:"date";i:1358816760;s:7:"content";s:2846:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/white-samsung-ativ-smart-pc-south-korea/"><img alt="White Samsung ATIV Smart PC launches in South Korea, remains the same inside" data-src-height="340" data-src-width="479" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/01/samativw1.jpg"></a></p><p> There's obviously <em>something </em>about gadgets <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/02/28/nokia-n900-in-white-hands-on/">dressed in white livery</a> that attracts plenty of consumers, and thus it shouldn't come as a surprise to see Samsung introduce a bleached model of its own <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/12/05/samsung-ativ-smart-pc-att-review/">ATIV Smart PC</a>. Unfortunately for some, however, the maker of the Galaxy line is keeping this particular launch local, with the white ATIV Smart PC set to be an exclusive to South Koreans -- well, at least for the time being. Regardless, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/tag/samsung/">Samsung's</a> Windows 8 hybrid remains unchanged otherwise, meaning there's still that same 11.6-inch, 1,366 x 768 display, a 1.8GHz, dual-core Clover Trail processor, 4,800 mAh battery and 64GB of onboard storage. The frosted <a href="http://www.engadget.com/tag/ATIV/">ATIV </a>device is on sale now for <span>1,090,000 won (around $1,000) -- but, hey, because we know there are likely would-be buyers outside of South Korea, we have a gallery past the jump to show what's being missed.</span><span><div><p><strong>Gallery: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/samsung-ativ-smart-pc-in-white/">Samsung ATIV Smart PC in white</a></strong></p><a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/samsung-ativ-smart-pc-in-white/5587014"><img src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/01/samativw2_thumbnail.jpg" alt="" title=""></a><a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/samsung-ativ-smart-pc-in-white/5587015"><img src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/01/samativw3_thumbnail.jpg" alt="" title=""></a><a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/samsung-ativ-smart-pc-in-white/5587016"><img src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/01/samativw4_thumbnail.jpg" alt="" title=""></a></div></span></p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/laptops/" rel="tag">Laptops</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/tablets/" rel="tag">Tablets</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/samsung/" rel="tag">Samsung</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/white-samsung-ativ-smart-pc-south-korea/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Via:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://sammyhub.com/2013/01/21/samsung-unveils-white-ativ-smart-pc-in-south-korea/">SammyHub</a><!--//--></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.samsung.com/global/ativ/ativ_pc.html">Samsung</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:8:"Engadget";}s:32:"f3de8087a77027b81d84c1b75ba12904";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:55:"This Is What It Looks Like to Be Spiderman in Real Life";s:4:"link";s:110:"http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~3/BdyaVosSKVE/this-is-what-it-looks-like-to-be-spiderman-in-real-life";s:6:"author";s:10:"Casey Chan";s:4:"date";i:1358815250;s:7:"content";s:2384:"<div> <!-- div style="background-color: #B3B3B3; width: 190px; padding: 1px;"><a title="Click here to read This Is What It Looks Like to Be Spiderman in Real Life" href="http://gizmodo.com/watch-this/" style="background-color:#8888