resher, the waterproof Xperia Tablet Z features a <span>bafflingly thin chassis (6.9mm), a </span><span>10.1-inch 1,920 x 1,200 display, a 1.5GHz quad-core processor, 2GB of RAM, an 8.1 megapixel camera and Android 4.1. If a poorly lit picture isn't enough to satisfy your curiosity, an equally dim video showcasing the unreleased device's UI has made its way to the web as well. Head past the break for a closer look at the Xperia Tablet Z in action.</span></p><p> <strong>Update:</strong> To be clear, the video below is an alleged leak of the Xperia Tablet Z's software running on an ASUS Transformer.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/tablets/" rel="tag">Tablets</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/sony/" rel="tag">Sony</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/sony-xperia-tablet-z-video/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Via:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://androidcommunity.com/sony-xperia-tablet-z-smiles-for-the-camera-in-leaked-video-20130121/">Android Community</a><!--//--></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.weibo.com/">Weibo (translated)</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:8:"Engadget";}s:32:"c66d63f6b30e84cdb511291c1cf69780";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:53:"Brin wears his Google glasses on NYC subway: Um, why?";s:4:"link";s:56:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/cnet/tcoc/~3/6-DDwpR38gA/";s:6:"author";s:16:"Chris Matyszczyk";s:4:"date";i:1358799898;s:7:"content";s:859:"Looking for all the world like a jewel thief, Google's co-founder is spotted on New York's most pristine mode of public transportation wearing the future on his nose. <a href="http://news.cnet.com/8301-17852_3-57565018-71/brin-wears-his-google-glasses-on-nyc-subway-um-why/?part=rss&amp;subj=news&amp;tag=readMore">[Read more]</a><img width="1" height="1" src="http://cnet.com.feedsportal.com/c/34938/f/645093/s/27c0d070/mf.gif" border="0"><br><br><a href="htt